# Artifacts that execute on the Linux capture VM (uploaded by labs/orchestrator) must
# stay LF, or a Windows checkout with core.autocrlf=true will CRLF-break bash, auditctl,
# and bpftrace on the VM. A .gitattributes only governs its own subtree, so this MUST
# live at the repo root to reach both labs/orchestrator/ and labs/linux/.
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.bt    text eol=lf
*.rules text eol=lf
*.py    text eol=lf

# Windows/macOS harness scripts: keep LF too (PowerShell Core handles LF fine).
*.ps1   text eol=lf
